				    <div class="inner">
				        <div class="comment-content">
				            <p>Hey.</p>

<p><br />
I've had a couple scares with my glove while lowering it for the trick. One time at Yankee Stadium, way back in the early 90s, a security guard on the field yanked the glove out of my hand and snapped the string. He threatened to confiscate the glove, but ended up returning it after batting practice. Last year at Shea, my string got caught in some tiny gap in the left field wall, and I needed help from one of the players to untangle it. But that's about it.</p>

<p></p>

<p>Usually, I buy the cheapest tickets and then move around, but sometimes, if there's a seat for sale in the PERFECT foul ball spot, I'll spring for it.</p>

<p></p>

<p>Sorry to hear you had such a tough time in Philly...but hey, it makes for a good story.</p>
