As I've told other people above, SORRY for the delayed reply. Since this entry is so old, I don't check it as often to see if people have commented. But anyway, the best piece of advice I can give you is to read other old entries about the games I've attended. I talk about EVERYTHING I do to get balls, so that's really the best way to pick up lots of tips. Just make sure you attend batting practice and bring a glove, and remember that you can get lots of balls thrown to you by the players if you position yourself in the right spot and say the right things.</p>

